President Muhammadu Buhari  has kicked against the tenure elongation of the All Progressive Congress (APC) National Working Commitee (NWC), led by John Oyegun, chairman of the party. He made this known on Tuesday in Abuja during a meeting at the Party's Headquaters. He asked the national excutive commitee (NEC) of the party to consider reversing the tenure extension of the NWC. He pointed out that the elongation is not in the party's constitution. more details soon